H0.text: Britain's first jet fighter, The Meteor was made by which company. De Havilland

H1.text: Britain's first jet fighter, The Meteor was made by which company. Supermarine

H2.text: Britain's first jet fighter, The Meteor was made by which company. Hawker

H3.text: Britain's first jet fighter, The Meteor was made by which company. GLOSTER

A4.text: The jet design became the Gloster Meteor, the only jet to be used in combat by the Allied Forces during the Second World War.

A5.text: This was followed by the Meteor, the RAF's first jet-powered fighter and the only Allied jet fighter to be put into service during the Second World War.
